cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.SE 

The paper deals with techniques for reducing the size of nondeterministic tree automata, which is a topic related to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also mentions the use of algorithms for merging states and removing transitions, which are common techniques in logic and set theory (cs.LO). The implementation of the algorithm on a library for tree automata (libvata) suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), while the exploration of how the algorithm can improve hard operations like complementation suggests a focus on programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
